-- This paper explains that market anomalies occur because "newswatchers" only focus on fundamental news and "momentum traders" only watch price trends, with neither group seeing the whole picture. This separation causes prices to initially underreact as news spreads slowly (diffuse into the price), which then triggers trend-chasing that inevitably pushes prices past their fair value into an overreaction.
